  "text": "Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO, USA) dissolved in PBS solution at 37°C overnight [CITATION_1] . The AAPH was then neutralized by adding 10 mM Vitamin C [CITATION_2] . Aliquots of the oxidized ALA, or the AAPH-oxidized surfactant mixture as a control, were then added to molten NGA media. For oxylipin treatments, 9S-hydroperoxy-10E,12Z,15Z-octadecatrienoic acid (9(S)-HpOTrE) and 13S-hydroperoxy-9Z,11E,15Z-octadecatrienoic acid (13(S)-HpOTrE) were purchased from Cayman Chemical (Ann Arbor, Michigan) and dissolved in 100% ethanol at 2 mM concentration. The chemicals, or an equal volume of 100% ethanol as a control, were then added to molten NGA media to produce plates with a final compound concentration of 0.2 mM. For combined ALA and 9(S)-HpOTrE treatments, 9(S)-HpOTrE, or an equal volume of 100% ethanol, was added along with ALA to molten NGA to give a final concentration of 0.2 mM 9(S)-HpOTrE and 5 mM ALA.",
